{
  "page": "Hyle Hunt",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hunt\" title=\"House Hunt\"><img alt=\"Hunt.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Hunt.png/50px-Hunt.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Hunt.png/75px-Hunt.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e1/Hunt.png/100px-Hunt.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Hyle Hunt</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hunt\" title=\"House Hunt\"><img alt=\"Hunt.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Hunt.png/50px-Hunt.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Hunt.png/75px-Hunt.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e1/Hunt.png/100px-Hunt.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Hyle Hunt by swordmaid.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/0f/Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png/350px-Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/0f/Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png/525px-Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/0f/Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png/700px-Hyle_Hunt_by_swordmaid.png 2x\" /></a><div>Hyle by Swordmaid</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></li><li>Captain<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hunt\" title=\"House Hunt\">House Hunt</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarly\" title=\"House Tarly\">House Tarly</a> (formerly)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Marcher</a> <small>(possibly)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafhyle_hunt.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafhyle_hunt.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">Bastard</a> girl<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Hyle Hunt</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hunt\" title=\"House Hunt\">House Hunt</a>. He is a <a href=\"/index.php/Household_knight\" title=\"Household knight\">household knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Horn_Hill\" title=\"Lord of Horn Hill\">Lord of Horn Hill</a>, and is one of his captains.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Hyle\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Hyle</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Hyle\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Hyle</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Hyle has a plain face, shaggy brown hair, hazel eyes, a cleft chin, a crooked nose, and a scar near his left ear.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He is one head shorter than <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>, who is about six and a half feet tall, putting Hyle at roughly five feet and ten inches in height.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Hyle has a full, rich laugh.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Hyle is a gallant,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> eloquent,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> stubborn,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and languid young man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He enjoys <a href=\"/index.php/Mead\" title=\"Mead\">mead</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Hyle wears a white surcoat with the arms of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hunt\" title=\"House Hunt\">House Hunt</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He wields a <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">sword</a> and rides a chestnut <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">courser</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Hyle keeps sheepskin maps in his boot.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ser Hyle served <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarly\" title=\"House Tarly\">House Tarly</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_Hill\" title=\"Horn Hill\">Horn Hill</a>. When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> tried to teach his son <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell</a> to swim by throwing him in a pond, Hyle had to rescue Sam.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Hyle knows of at least one <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> that he has fathered, a girl. Her mother doused Hyle with a kettle of soup the last time he visited his daughter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>While at <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a> after the outbreak of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Edmund_Ambrose\" title=\"Edmund Ambrose\">Edmund Ambrose</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ben_Bushy\" title=\"Ben Bushy\">Ben Bushy</a>, and Hyle began a wager on taking <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenhead\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maidenhead\">maidenhead</a>. In Hyle's attempt to woo Brienne, he brought her an illuminated book, apples and carrots for her horses, and a blue silk plume for her helm. He told her camp gossip, said things to make her smile, and even trained with her once. Other knights then began trying to impress Brienne, including Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Richard_Farrow\" title=\"Richard Farrow\">Richard Farrow</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Beesbury\" title=\"Hugh Beesbury\">Hugh Beesbury</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Mark_Mullendore\" title=\"Mark Mullendore\">Mark Mullendore</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Will_the_Stork\" title=\"Will the Stork\">Will the Stork</a>. When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> heard about the wager, he put an end to it, but blamed Brienne for the knights' behavior.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Randyll <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_Maidenpool\" title=\"Taking of Maidenpool\">takes Maidenpool</a>, Hyle commands one of <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">the town's</a> gates. He encounters Brienne,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> who has been tasked by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> with finding <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and laments his current predicament.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Tarly has Hyle follow Brienne, <a href=\"/index.php/Dick_Crabb\" title=\"Dick Crabb\">Dick Crabb</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a> as they travel to <a href=\"/index.php/Crackclaw_Point\" title=\"Crackclaw Point\">Crackclaw Point</a>, instructing him to bring Sansa back to Maidenpool if Brienne is successful in her search for the girl.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> The knight catches up with Brienne at the <a href=\"/index.php/Whispers\" title=\"Whispers\">Whispers</a>, where she slays <a href=\"/index.php/Shagwell\" title=\"Shagwell\">Shagwell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pyg\" title=\"Pyg\">Pyg</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Timeon\" title=\"Timeon\">Timeon</a>, formerly of the <a href=\"/index.php/Brave_Companions\" title=\"Brave Companions\">Brave Companions</a>. After helping to bury Dick,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Hyle insists on bringing the slain <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaws\" title=\"Outlaws\">outlaws</a>' heads back to Maidenpool so Lord Tarly can display them on the town's walls. Hyle does not take credit for killing the outlaws, but instead informs Randyll of Brienne's valor. However, Lord Tarly attributes Brienne's victory only to her <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">sword</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Oathkeeper\" title=\"Oathkeeper\">Oathkeeper</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Lord Tarly dismisses Hyle from his service, Hyle joins Brienne in her quest, expecting a rich reward if he finds Sansa. The knight suggests that Brienne accompany <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Meribald\" title=\"Meribald\">Meribald</a> on his circuit through the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> During their stay at the <a href=\"/index.php/Quiet_Isle\" title=\"Quiet Isle\">Quiet Isle</a>, Hyle is intrigued when the <a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)\" title=\"Elder Brother (Quiet Isle)\">Elder Brother</a> mentions that the <a href=\"/index.php/Holy_brother\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy brother\">brothers</a> have found six of <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaegar Targaryen\">Rhaegar Targaryen</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Ruby\" title=\"Ruby\">rubies</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Brienne's party sees the destructive results of the <a href=\"/index.php/Raid_on_Saltpans\" title=\"Raid on Saltpans\">raid</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Saltpans\" title=\"Saltpans\">Saltpans</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>As they near the <a href=\"/index.php/Crossroads_inn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crossroads inn\">crossroads inn</a>, Hyle recognizes that the bodies of men hanging near the road, with chunks of <a href=\"/index.php/Salt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Salt\">salt</a> shoved into their mouths, must be the perpetrators of Saltpans. In the inn's common room, Hyle asks for Brienne's hand in <a href=\"/index.php/Marriage\" title=\"Marriage\">marriage</a>, but she rejects him. Brienne intends to leave Hyle behind at the inn while he is sleeping, but her plan is interrupted by the arrival of <a href=\"/index.php/Rorge\" title=\"Rorge\">Rorge</a>, who had <a href=\"/index.php/Hound\" title=\"Hound\">led the assault on Saltpans</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Biter\" title=\"Biter\">Biter</a>, and five other former Brave Companions. Brienne kllls Rorge when he threatens <a href=\"/index.php/Willow_Heddle\" title=\"Willow Heddle\">Willow Heddle</a>, and as she battles Biter she thinks she hears Hyle joining the fight against the other outlaws.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Gendry\" title=\"Gendry\">Gendry</a> saves Brienne from Biter as the brute bites her face.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the encounter with the outlaws at the inn, Hyle, Brienne, and Podrick are taken prisoner by those sworn to <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Stoneheart\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lady Stoneheart\">Lady Stoneheart</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_banners\" title=\"Brotherhood without banners\">brotherhood without banners</a> beat Hyle until his face is almost unrecognizable. Despite Brienne's insistence that Hyle is innocent of any crimes, he is judged guilty for allying himself with <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> and is sentenced to death. Lady Stoneheart commands Brienne to kill Jaime Lannister to free herself and her companions, to choose \"sword or noose\", but Brienne refuses to. Hyle offers to kill Jaime in Brienne's stead, and <a href=\"/index.php/Lem\" title=\"Lem\">Lem</a> strikes him in the face. Hyle is hanged alongside Podrick and Brienne, although Brienne shouts \"sword\" to intervene.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm6425.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm6425.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Hyle\">Quotes by Hyle</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Hyle\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hyle</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">His lordship</a> informed me that he had no further need of my sword, or my insolence. It amounts to the same thing. Henceforth I shall enjoy the adventuresome life of a <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_knight\" title=\"Hedge knight\">hedge knight</a> ... though if we do find <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a>, I imagine we will be well rewarded.<br />\n</p><p><b>Brienne</b>: I mean to save the girl, not sell her. I swore a vow.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Hyle</b>: I don't recall that I did.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Hyle and <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hyle</b>: Your heart is as mushy as <a href=\"/index.php/Meribald\" title=\"Meribald\">our septon's</a> porridge. Can it be? Somewhere inside our swordswench is a mother just squirming to give birth. What you really want is a sweet pink babe to suckle at your teat. You need a man for that, I hear. A husband, preferably. Why not me?<br />\n</p><p><b>Brienne</b>: If you still hope to win your wager—<br />\n</p>\n<b>Hyle</b>: What I want to win is you, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Selwyn_Tarth\" title=\"Selwyn Tarth\">Selwyn's</a> only living child. I've known men to wed <a href=\"/index.php/Lackwit\" title=\"Lackwit\">lackwits</a> and suckling babes for prizes a tenth the size of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a>. I am not <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a>, I confess it, but I have the virtue of being still amongst the living. Some would say that is my only virtue. <a href=\"/index.php/Marriage\" title=\"Marriage\">Marriage</a> would serve the both of us.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Hyle to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hyle</b>: In the dark you'd be as beautiful as any other woman. Your lips were made for kissing.<br />\n</p><p><b>Brienne</b>: They are lips. All lips are the same.<br />\n<b>Hyle</b>: And all lips are made for kissing. Leave your chamber door unbarred tonight, and I will steal into your bed and prove the truth of what I say.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Brienne</b>: If you do, you'll be a <a href=\"/index.php/Eunuch\" title=\"Eunuch\">eunuch</a> when you leave.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Hyle and <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>My lady, you should have wed me when I made my offer. Now I fear you're doomed to die a <a href=\"/index.php/Maid\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maid\">maid</a>, and me a poor man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Hyle to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Hyle\">Quotes about Hyle</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Hyle\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>You think too much.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> to Hyle</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Podrick</b>: What did he do to you, ser? I mean, my lady.<br />\n<b>Brienne</b>: At <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a>, when King <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly</a> called his banners, some men played a game with me. Ser Hyle was one of them. It was a cruel game, hurtful and unchivalrous.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Hyle Hunt was no <a href=\"/index.php/True_knight\" title=\"True knight\">true knight</a>. His honest face was just a <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummer</a>'s mask. I do not need his help, I do not need his protection, and I do not need him, she told herself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Ser Hyle Hunt is a gallant from the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Meribald\" title=\"Meribald\">Meribald</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Narbert\" title=\"Narbert\">Narbert</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Tarlys are stated to be <a href=\"/index.php/Marcher_lords\" title=\"Marcher lords\">Marcher lords</a> in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>. As the Hunts are sworn to the Tarlys, they most likely reside in the same region.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hyle_Hunt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.01</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.02</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.03</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.04</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.05</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.06</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.07</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\">1.08</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\">1.09</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\">1.10</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Brienne III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafhyle_hunt.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafhyle_hunt.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Hyle Hunt.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\">3.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\">3.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\">3.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.